"{\"uid\": \"smh.com.au-national-the-treasurer-who-delivered-nine-balanced-budgets-and-an-olympics-20240201-p5f1lp.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are sorry, this feature is currently unavailable.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are working to restore it.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please try again later.\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was published1yearago  Add articles to your saved list and come back to them any time.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MICHAEL EGAN: 1948-2024  Michael Rueben Egan,who died on Wednesday, was the longest serving NSW treasurer, from 1995 to 2005.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 201, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"MICHAEL EGAN\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His ministerial career and terms in both houses of the NSW parliament, as well as his subsequent achievements, including as Chancellor of Macquarie University, make him deserving of a State funeral.\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 382, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1361183932977582e-48, \"text\": \"Macquarie University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_funeral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"State funeral\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_funeral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_funeral\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former NSW State Treasurer Michael Egan at Parliament House, 2008.Credit:Fairfax  But he decided to be buried simply at the Woronora Memorial Park, Sutherland, adjacent to where his parents are in the Catholic section of the cemetery, with priests at the graveside, but no earthly bother otherwise.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania_Treasurer\", \"score\": 0.7033200756813407, \"rank\": 0.22643530524464053, \"text\": \"State Treasurer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania_Treasurer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania_Treasurer\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 570, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_House,_Canberra\", \"score\": 0.8221447252922859, \"rank\": 0.053480319546277334, \"text\": \"Parliament House\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_House,_Canberra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_House,_Canberra\"}, {\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999921819835, \"rank\": 7.81559127015288e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This had a family precedent.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When his mother, Jean n\\u00e9e Brown (1923-2016) died, the notice in theHeraldread: \\\"At Jean's insistence, she will be buried without fuss or ceremony and, again at her request, without mourning.\\\"\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 1047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiden_and_married_names\", \"score\": 0.9989764927117052, \"rank\": 0.0010245559290461407, \"text\": \"n\\u00e9e\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiden_and_married_names\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiden_and_married_names\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This might imply a shy, retiring disposition at the heart of the family.\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was no such modesty.\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jean, a livewire, dynamic personality, whose fabled fashion shop in Caringbah, and her white house, manicured lawns and sprightly flower decorations on the Kingsway, Cronulla, were landmarks in the Shire.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.868907355554322e-34, \"text\": \"Caringbah\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\"}, {\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She lived the motto 'life is celebrated with the living, not the dead'.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan was born in Coogee, in Sydney's eastern suburbs, on February 21, 1948, the son of Jean and Stanley Joseph Egan, who served as a sergeant in the Royal Australian Artillery from 1939 to 1948.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Coogee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0005227542321039e-49, \"text\": \"Coogee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Coogee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Coogee\"}, {\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.100455070788724e-22, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_V._Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joseph Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_V._Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_V._Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 1576, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Australian_Artillery\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Royal Australian Artillery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Australian_Artillery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Australian_Artillery\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They married in 1942 and Michael was their only child.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a stubborn youngster, Egan insisted on a Catholic baptism, deeming his Anglican christening insufficient.\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999921819835, \"rank\": 7.81559127015288e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reared in Caringbah, then Cronulla, young Egan from third grade onwards went to St Patrick's College, the Christian Brothers school in Sutherland.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1797, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.868907355554322e-34, \"text\": \"Caringbah\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}, {\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9991736981203899, \"rank\": 0.0006938065930965277, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\", \"score\": 0.9999999949923222, \"rank\": 5.005192842007275e-09, \"text\": \"Brothers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\"}, {\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.410635821738757e-16, \"text\": \"Sutherland\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He completed a BA at the University of Sydney.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1949, \"end\": 1951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bachelor_of_Arts\", \"score\": 0.9999789549969919, \"rank\": 2.1039645919354796e-05, \"text\": \"BA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bachelor_of_Arts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bachelor_of_Arts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined the ALP in school shorts, in 1964, aged 16.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1995, \"end\": 1998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Egan was elected MP for Cronulla in 1978, aged thirty, on his fourth attempt (he also stood in 1971, '73, and '76), his parliamentary speeches, interjections, and buoyant turns of phrase, marked him as a future star and a favourite of NSW Premier Neville Wran.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}, {\"begin\": 2276, \"end\": 2287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW Premier\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Wran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neville Wran\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Wran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Wran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in NSW Labor politics, getting ahead is hard scrabble.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He knew luck mattered as well as determination to win friends in the party and beyond.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A strong sense of social justice, business acumen, and a flair for the theatrical Egan inherited from his mother.\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was an elegant, cheerful, generous, and kindly lady, a single parent after the premature death of her husband.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fit, gifted with dark good looks, curly hair, dominating dark-rim spectacles (in those days), he cut a lithe, hungry look, if a little on the short side.\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2832, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1980s and 1990s, Egan was one of the \\\"big guns\\\" at NSW ALP conferences.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Memorably he once said: \\\"The physical distance between having your ear to the ground and your head buried in the sand may not be great, but that difference makes all the difference.\\\"\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One measure of his career is that Egan was always mindful of that insight.\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan began active politics on the ALP Left, thinking the party's head office too conservative, but he never had any allegiance to Marxist elements in the ALP, and from the start he was instinctively wary of local Labor supremo (and alleged secret communist) Arthur Gietzelt, who dominated Shire politics back in the day.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marxism\", \"score\": 0.9990395928223224, \"rank\": 0.0009613304460498817, \"text\": \"Marxist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marxism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marxism\"}, {\"begin\": 3326, \"end\": 3329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 3385, \"end\": 3390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 3430, \"end\": 3436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.874693427474453e-12, \"text\": \"Arthur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\"}, {\"begin\": 3461, \"end\": 3466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249000429859319e-22, \"text\": \"Shire\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Employed as an Industrial Officer in the national office of the Australasian Meat Industries Employees Association, he was in good company.\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Future Keating staffer and noted journalist John Edwards, author of acclaimed biographies of Curtin and Keating, was a contemporary, also for a time employed by 'the meaties'.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3727, \"end\": 3733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Curtin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9990971609732295e-16, \"text\": \"Curtin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Curtin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Curtin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Whitlam years, until the government's defeat, Egan worked with Les Johnson, MP for Hughes, an electorate then based on Sutherland and surrounding suburbs.\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3881, \"end\": 3892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.902333021494056e-21, \"text\": \"Les Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 3901, \"end\": 3907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billy_Hughes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.676322013342198e-25, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billy_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billy_Hughes\"}, {\"begin\": 3937, \"end\": 3947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.410635821738757e-16, \"text\": \"Sutherland\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then came public service, as a complaints officer in the State Pollution Control Commission.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Involvement in politics taught him to greatly respect Whitlam's contribution and almost seamlessly he came to identify with the NSW Right, believing the best of that tradition lay in innovative, practical, reforms, alert to public sentiment as well as seized by the determination to make a difference to ordinary people's lives.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4121, \"end\": 4128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gough_Whitlam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.158420965161067e-20, \"text\": \"Whitlam\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gough_Whitlam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gough_Whitlam\"}, {\"begin\": 4195, \"end\": 4198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Treasurer Michael Egan announces the commencement of construction for the $225 million Master Plan redevelopments at Taronga and Western Plains Zoos, 2002.Credit:Fairfax  He believed personal leadership mattered.\", \"from\": 4397, \"to\": 4609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4407, \"end\": 4419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 4559, \"end\": 4566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of his first speeches in the NSW parliament, he said ministers had to take responsibility for their actions, and not hide behind public servants: \\\"The task of a minister is \\u2026to make the difficult decisions of government, [not] to leave them to independent public servants while he jumps up and down on the back seat of a ministerial car.\\\"\", \"from\": 4610, \"to\": 4955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4646, \"end\": 4660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had the gift of the gab, the verbal jab too, but was good-humoured and, mostly, widely respected across both sides of his politics, with the ALP Left, and with his Liberal and National party opponents.\", \"from\": 4957, \"to\": 5161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From 1981 to 1984 as chair of the NSW Public Accounts Committee, Egan authored landmark reports on, and audit reviews of, government programs.\", \"from\": 5163, \"to\": 5305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5197, \"end\": 5200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 5201, \"end\": 5226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_accounts_committee\", \"score\": 0.9999611130136701, \"rank\": 3.8888498342307806e-05, \"text\": \"Public Accounts Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_accounts_committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_accounts_committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was destined for the ministry, until narrowly defeated in 1984 as MP for Cronulla.\", \"from\": 5306, \"to\": 5391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5382, \"end\": 5390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A strong personal vote was not enough to sandbank him from the big anti-Labor swing that year.\", \"from\": 5393, \"to\": 5487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Labor has never come close to winning Cronulla again.\", \"from\": 5488, \"to\": 5541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5488, \"end\": 5493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5526, \"end\": 5534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shows Premier Bob Carr and Treasurer Michael Egan at State Parliament prior to announcing the budget, 1995.Credit:Fairfax  Egan then worked for future premier Barrie Unsworth, who was a great mentor.\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5557, \"end\": 5560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9993124870684011, \"rank\": 0.0006878034058488228, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 5580, \"end\": 5592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 5602, \"end\": 5612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9981137129078984, \"rank\": 0.0018875769491013498, \"text\": \"Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5657, \"end\": 5664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 5702, \"end\": 5717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barrie Unsworth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Selected to invigorate Labor in the Upper House, he served in the NSW Legislative Council beginning in 1986.\", \"from\": 5743, \"to\": 5851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5766, \"end\": 5771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5779, \"end\": 5790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\", \"score\": 0.9998654330011266, \"rank\": 0.0001345851094959585, \"text\": \"Upper House\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\"}, {\"begin\": 5809, \"end\": 5832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW Legislative Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bob Carr was one of his champions.\", \"from\": 5852, \"to\": 5886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5852, \"end\": 5855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9993124870684011, \"rank\": 0.0006878034058488228, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In opposition Egan, in a daring act of invention styled himself as the \\\"Chair of the NSW Waste Watch Committee\\\", getting much more attention than any of the sleepy performers among his colleagues.\", \"from\": 5888, \"to\": 6084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That role attracted great media attention in his imaginative criticisms of the then Greiner and Fahey governments.\", \"from\": 6086, \"to\": 6200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1990, he was narrowly defeated in a ballot of colleagues as Deputy Leader of Labor in the Legislative Council.\", \"from\": 6201, \"to\": 6314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6294, \"end\": 6313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.744881372490074e-23, \"text\": \"Legislative Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1991, however, he was clearly the deserving leader of the ALP, and Leader of the Opposition, in the Chamber.\", \"from\": 6315, \"to\": 6426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6376, \"end\": 6379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything seemed to prepare him for the most important role of his life, NSW treasurer, which he took on when Bob Carr led Labor to victory in 1995.\", \"from\": 6428, \"to\": 6577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6502, \"end\": 6505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 6539, \"end\": 6542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9993124870684011, \"rank\": 0.0006878034058488228, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 6552, \"end\": 6557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Treasurer Michael Egan addressing the journalists about the budget, 1999.Credit:Fairfax  Treasury officials admired his hands-on management, which drew on the talent around him, and in a probing, collegiate manner, he asked questions as to how the state's resources could be better managed.\", \"from\": 6579, \"to\": 6869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6589, \"end\": 6601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 6659, \"end\": 6666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 6668, \"end\": 6676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Treasury\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.799924981749297e-16, \"text\": \"Treasury\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Treasury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Treasury\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was ably assisted by a strong ministerial staff and Egan personally sponsored the public service career of Michael Coutts-Trotter, who went on to be Secretary of Premier & Cabinet, as well as, now, secretary to the NSW Treasury.\", \"from\": 6870, \"to\": 7101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6980, \"end\": 7002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Coutts-Trotter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Coutts-Trotter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Coutts-Trotter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Coutts-Trotter\"}, {\"begin\": 7088, \"end\": 7100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Treasury\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW Treasury\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Treasury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Treasury\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As treasurer in the Carr government, Egan was responsible for safeguarding NSW's AAA credit rating.\", \"from\": 7103, \"to\": 7202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7178, \"end\": 7181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 7184, \"end\": 7187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999687590730632, \"rank\": 3.123488957870851e-05, \"text\": \"AAA\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He relentlessly focused on introducing market tests for government enterprises.\", \"from\": 7203, \"to\": 7282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He delivered nine balanced budgets on a net lending basis, eliminated government net debt and fully funded the Sydney Olympics.\", \"from\": 7283, \"to\": 7410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not everything went smoothly, but Egan is remembered as the engine of reform innovation in the NSW government.\", \"from\": 7412, \"to\": 7522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7507, \"end\": 7510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He favoured electricity privatisation in Carr's first term, but union opposition put a stop to what he saw for NSW a lucrative bargain: high prices for selling electricity generation assets in exchange for reinvesting in transport and social infrastructure.\", \"from\": 7523, \"to\": 7780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7634, \"end\": 7637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He supported Premier Morris Iemma's abortive efforts along the same lines in 2008.\", \"from\": 7782, \"to\": 7864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7803, \"end\": 7815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Iemma\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Morris Iemma\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Iemma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Iemma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan always thought: \\\"if we do not do this, the Tories will.\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7913, \"end\": 7919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6514773368375486e-15, \"text\": \"Tories\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they will skewer the priorities away from where it matters most.\\\"\", \"from\": 7926, \"to\": 7995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Demonstration against the proposed Michael Egan tax on poker machines in NSW clubs in the city, 2003.Credit:Fairfax  In frustration, he resigned from the ALP when John Robertson became NSW opposition leader in 2011 and rejoined when \\\"Robbo\\\" lost his role in 2014.\", \"from\": 7997, \"to\": 8260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8032, \"end\": 8044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 8070, \"end\": 8073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 8105, \"end\": 8112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 8151, \"end\": 8154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 8160, \"end\": 8174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_S._Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.877260998301341e-14, \"text\": \"John Robertson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_S._Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_S._Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 8182, \"end\": 8203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(New_South_Wales)\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW opposition leader\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(New_South_Wales)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(New_South_Wales)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan was still smarting over Robinson's actions in 2001, when the latter was secretary of Unions NSW.\", \"from\": 8261, \"to\": 8362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8290, \"end\": 8298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\", \"score\": 0.9719854895945259, \"rank\": 0.02880839232989489, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\"}, {\"begin\": 8351, \"end\": 8361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labor_Council_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Unions NSW\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q178790\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labor_Council_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labor_Council_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At that time, Robertson led a blockade of the NSW parliament over workers' compensation law reforms.\", \"from\": 8364, \"to\": 8464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8378, \"end\": 8387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7856593650651004e-22, \"text\": \"Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 8410, \"end\": 8424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for priorities, in politics it's an advantage to have a memory and aptitude to complete the unfinished.\", \"from\": 8466, \"to\": 8572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two examples:  On Egan's urging, in 1987, Premier Unsworth offered Cardinal Clancy full funding for completion of the spires of St Mary's Cathedral as part of the Bicentennial.\", \"from\": 8574, \"to\": 8750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8624, \"end\": 8632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.235177088259642e-57, \"text\": \"Unsworth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\"}, {\"begin\": 8705, \"end\": 8709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_I_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9988175853463411, \"rank\": 0.0011350804262330672, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_I_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_I_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But His Eminence hesitated, preferring a public appeal from parishioners, emphasising the building was built from the pennies and threepences donated by the working poor.\", \"from\": 8751, \"to\": 8921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Egan was Treasurer, the Expenditure Review Committee of Cabinet granted $5m to cover the outstanding funding deficit, matching funds already raised, to enable the spires to be finally completed in 2000.\", \"from\": 8922, \"to\": 9129, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The back-to-school bonus that Premier Unsworth tried to introduce in 1987 and resisted in Cabinet, was then introduced by Egan with little fanfare in 1995, in his first Budget.\", \"from\": 9131, \"to\": 9307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9169, \"end\": 9177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.235177088259642e-57, \"text\": \"Unsworth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\"}, {\"begin\": 9221, \"end\": 9228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cabinet_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999545980255, \"rank\": 4.538887375310601e-08, \"text\": \"Cabinet\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cabinet_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cabinet_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Post politics, chosen by his peers on the Macquarie University Council as Chancellor, he proudly drove changes, sponsored a new medical faculty, and initiated a building program which transformed the appearance of the university.\", \"from\": 9309, \"to\": 9538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9351, \"end\": 9371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1361183932977582e-48, \"text\": \"Macquarie University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Attending 268 graduations ceremonies, he conferred almost 40,000 degrees usually with charm, alacrity, and wit.\", \"from\": 9540, \"to\": 9651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The graduation hall was renamed Michael Egan Hall in March 2022.\", \"from\": 9652, \"to\": 9716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9684, \"end\": 9696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On that occasion, the University awarded its longest-serving Chancellor an Honorary Doctorate.\", \"from\": 9717, \"to\": 9811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Former NSW Treasuer Michael Egan giving evidence to a state parliamentary committee examining Sydney's cross city tunnel contract, 2005.Credit:Fairfax  Egan was hard on himself, assiduously working in public roles until kidney problems and diminishing health made that impossible.\", \"from\": 9813, \"to\": 10093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9833, \"end\": 9845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 9907, \"end\": 9913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.100455070788724e-22, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 9956, \"end\": 9963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was grateful for the many kindnesses of staff at the Wolper Hospital, Woollahra, where he lived his last days.\", \"from\": 10094, \"to\": 10207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10167, \"end\": 10176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Municipality_of_Woollahra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.343480850731188e-14, \"text\": \"Woollahra\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Municipality_of_Woollahra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Municipality_of_Woollahra\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Intensely private, Egan is survived by his life companion Byron Addison.\", \"from\": 10209, \"to\": 10281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10267, \"end\": 10272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Byron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6253900009830185e-36, \"text\": \"Byron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Byron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Byron\"}, {\"begin\": 10273, \"end\": 10280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Addison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.737306171255843e-64, \"text\": \"Addison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Addison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Addison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get a weekly wrap of views that will challenge, champion and inform your own.Sign up for our Opinion newsletter.\", \"from\": 10283, \"to\": 10395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a92025\", \"from\": 10397, \"to\": 10412, \"entities\": []}]}"